 Measurement ORDER within a tunnel session correlates with physical POSITION (the person walks along the beamline). Position correlates with dose and\
 degradation. So a raw correlation of differential vs. order could be spurious.\
\
 Controls:\
 1. Check whether the sign of correlation is consistent across sessions (drift = consistent sign; position = depends on walk direction)\
 2. After computing per-session correlations, report the sign pattern\
 3. Optionally group by region and check within-region order effects\
