\f1\b Verification
\f0\b0 \
\
 After the script runs:\
 1. Visually inspect all 4 plots\
 2. Cross-check Analysis 1 slot timing against a few raw .dat files manually\
 3. Verify Analysis 2 Spearman values by hand for one small session (e.g., 2025-10-23, 9 plates)\
 4. Confirm Y-14 values match the raw .dat file contents exactly\
 5. Check that the pooled N matches expected total (sum of plates across 7 sessions)\
\
 
\f1\b Interpretation
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Guide
\f0\b0 \
\
 - If pooled |rho| < 0.15 and p > 0.1 \uc0\u8594  within-session drift does NOT affect the differential; "cancels by construction" validated empirically. No error\
 budget change needed.\
 - If pooled |rho| > 0.3 and p < 0.05 AND sign is consistent across sessions \uc0\u8594  potential within-session effect. Estimate slope, quantify bias, assess error\
 budget impact.\
 - If rho is significant but sign flips across sessions \uc0\u8594  likely position confound, not drift. Report as such.\
\
