   That's 15x larger than NdFeB's total capture. Yet SmCo shows zero degradation.\
\
   Resolution: Neutron capture alone doesn't cause demagnetization. The material must also be VULNERABLE to the deposited energy. SmCo resists because:\
   1. Higher Curie temperature (820C vs 315C): thermal spike zones are smaller because more energy is needed to locally exceed Tc\
   2. Higher anisotropy field (3.6x): domain reversal requires a stronger demagnetizing field, so even if Tc is exceeded locally, reversal is less likely\
\
   Combined: SmCo is predicted to be roughly 7x more resistant per thermal spike event.\
\
