   diameter) above the Curie temperature. When this zone cools, if the local demagnetizing field exceeds the coercive field, irreversible domain reversal\
   occurs.\
\
   Panel (a): SmCo has 1.9x higher Curie temp (Kelvin) and 3.6x higher anisotropy field than NdFeB. Combined, the model predicts SmCo should be roughly 7x\
