   Candidate explanations for the gap:\
   1. Multiple cascade events from secondary particles (not just primary neutrons)\
   2. Dy grain boundary amplification (damage concentrated at structurally critical boundaries)\
   3. Sub-threshold cumulative damage (many small perturbations below Tc that collectively reduce remanence)\
   4. Local fluence underestimate (ambient dosimetry doesn't capture local beam loss)\
\
   We are honest that the quantitative prediction doesn't match. The qualitative agreement (SmCo immune, NdFeB degraded, Dy amplification) is strong.""")\
