\f0\b0  Dave raises a legitimate confound that we cannot fully rule out with current data, but the N42EH > N52SH inversion is very hard to explain\
  with thermal aging and very naturally explained by Dy neutron capture. The aging hypothesis and the radiation hypothesis are not mutually exclusive; some\
  component of the signal could be aging. Getting the Honeywell temperature data (Task 6) has gone from "nice to have" to "essential."\
\
  What did Gemini say?\
