\f0\b0  
\f1\b the
\f0\b0  
\f1\b differential:
\f0\b0  
\f1\b almost
\f0\b0  
\f1\b nothing
\f0\b0  
\f1\b changes.
\f0\b0  All 4 slots on a plate are measured in the same order, within ~2 minutes. The time delay between Helmholtz\
  and Teslameter is the same for all 4. So whatever temperature bias the delay introduces, it's common-mode and cancels in the NdFeB-SmCo difference. At\
  0.066%/C differential sensitivity and a room warming at ~1-2 C/hour, a 3-minute delay means ~0.05-0.1 C drift, which is ~0.003-0.007% on the differential.\
  That's 4-10x below the statistical noise floor (0.028%).\
\
  
