\f1\b 2)
\f0\b0 . Here's why:\
\
  Right now, the Teslameter temperature 
\f3\i always
\f0\i0  lags the Helmholtz/Arduino measurement by 1-5 minutes. That means the observed +1.0 C mean offset (Teslameter\
  minus Arduino) could be a mix of:\
\
  1. Real probe self-heating bias (would persist regardless of order)\
  2. Real thermal lag in the sample (sample warmer than air; would persist regardless of order)\
  3. Room warming during the delay (would 
\f3\i flip
\f0\i0  
\f3\i sign
\f0\i0  if you reverse the order)\
\
  With the current protocol, you 
\f1\b cannot
\f0\b0  
